# Rate limiting

- Apply rate limits at the API gateway or middleware layer before business logic.
- Use token bucket or sliding window algorithms; fixed windows cause burst edge cases.
- Limit by user ID, API key, or IP — prefer authenticated identity over IP when available.
- Return 429 with `Retry-After` header; include rate limit headers (`X-RateLimit-*`).
- Set stricter limits on expensive endpoints (LLM calls, exports, search).
- Whitelist internal services; do not rate-limit health checks.
- Log rate limit violations for abuse detection.
- Store counters in Redis for distributed rate limiting across instances.
- Gracefully degrade under load before hard rejection where UX allows (queue, slow mode).
- Test rate limits in integration tests with burst traffic simulation.
